participatory society in which the people played the leading role, one that loved peace and 
recognized the rights of historically excluded populations like Afro-descendant and 
indigenous people, farmers, women and people with disabilities. These rights had been 
concretized in 46 laws, thereby complying with the obligations established in international 
instruments: laws that ensured prior and informed consultations, intercultural and 
